==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swabber
<hw>Swab"ber</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>zwabber</ets>; cf.D.
<ets>zwabberen</ets> to swab, G. <ets>schwabbern</ets>, Dan.
<ets>svabre</ets>, Sw. <ets>svab</ets> a swab, <ets>svabla</ets> to
swab.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who swabs a floor or desk.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Formerly, an interior officer on
board of British ships of war, whose business it was to see that the
ship was kept clean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Same as <er>Swobber</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swad</ent>⟦br⟧
